transcript.text: Mary? Hi. Hello. I'm Susan Thompson, Resource Manager. Hi, I'm Mary Hansen and I'm applying
for one of your kitchen jobs. Great. Here's a copy of my resume. Great. Have a seat, Mary.
Thank you. Mary, do you have any experience working in the kitchen? No, but I want to
learn. I work hard and I cook a lot at home. Okay. Well, tell me about yourself. Well,
I love to learn new things. I'm very organized and I follow directions exactly. That's why
my boss at my last job made me a trainer. And the company actually gave me a special
certificate for coming to work on time every day for a year. And I'm taking an English class to
improve my writing skills. That's great. Why did you leave your last job? It was graveyard and I
need to work days. Oh, I see. Well, what hours can you work? From 8 a.m. until 5 p.m. Okay. Well,
Do you have any questions for me, Mary? Yes. What kind of training is needed? Not a lot. Most new
workers can learn everything the first day. Do you have any other questions? No, I don't think so,
but I've heard a lot of good things about your company and I would really like to work here.
Well, I have a few more interviews to do today, but I will call you tomorrow if you get the job.
Okay. It was sure nice to meet you. Nice meeting you too. Thank you so much for your time. Yes,

topics.label: Job Application Process
topics.description: Overview of the typical steps involved in applying and interviewing for a job.

summary.text: This segment covers the initiation of a job interview, including the candidate's introduction, sharing of resume, and the interviewer explaining the process. It highlights key interview interactions such as answering questions, asking questions, and concluding the interview.

topics.label: Candidate Qualifications and Skills
topics.description: Discussion of a candidates background, skills, and qualities relevant to the job.

summary.text: The candidate, Mary, shares her background, emphasizing her motivation to learn, organizational skills, and recognition as a trainer, despite lacking formal kitchen experience. She also mentions her commitment to punctuality and ongoing language improvement efforts.

topics.label: Job Requirements and Hours
topics.description: Information about the working hours and training expectations for the position.

summary.text: The interviewer discusses the typical training process, indicating minimal training needed, and addresses the applicants availability and preferred work hours, which are daytime shifts.

topics.label: Candidate Questions and Employer Responses
topics.description: Interaction where the candidate asks questions about the job and the employer responds.

summary.text: Mary asks about training requirements, and the interviewer reassures her that most new employees learn quickly. The interview closes with polite goodbyes and expressions of interest.
